We were better prepared for today.
We looked at what we did wrong last time round against them and knew we could be better. Last time it was about our weaknesses. This time it was about theirs. The boys deserved it today.
At %1s, we pride ourselves on our resilience.

Are %1s just a better team than you right now?
Tough to take for %1s fans: that's two defeats against %2s. Do you have to accept that they're just the better team right now?
We need our senior players to step up.

Yes, we've been beaten twice by %1s now. And that hurts. But I believe in my players. We'll learn our lessons and improve. I'm looking to the senior players to set an example now. They're the guys who we need to lead us forward from here.
We have work to do defensively.

Man for man, I think our lads should be a match for anybody but, if you look at those two defeats, you can see something's not right. We have to be tougher and more difficult to beat. We need to work hard on our organisation. We'll be back on the training pitch in the morning.
You have to learn from setbacks.

A defeat and then a draw. You just can't seem to get the better of them. How do you improve? Where is the problem as you see it?
We will stick together, I promise you.
This isn't a time to be blaming anyone. We need to stick together and I need to come up with a better strategy ahead of our next game against them. We'll be better in future, I can promise you.
Maybe I need to make changes.

We haven't been able to control possession in either game against them. I have to make a decision. Do I go with a different team shape in future? Or do I need to look at changing personnel? We've just not been good enough.
We've played a lot of games recently.

It's always a tough, physical battle against these opponents. We've played a lot of games recently and just don't seem strong enough at the moment. The lads need to rest and recover. I know they can cause more problems for %1s than they have these past two games.
How did you get turned over this time round?
You must surely have been expecting to beat %1s again today. Instead, they've surprised you. How do you explain the difference between the two games?
We didn't handle the pressure.

I can only guess that the boys were feeling the pressure. People were expecting us to repeat our previous success. But being mentally strong is part of the game and we should have dealt with the situation better. I'm sure we will in future.

The lads gave it everything.
Of course results matter and this was a disappointing one. But I look at the performance, too, and the players' attitude. I can't be too unhappy with them. Today just wasn't our day.
We can't keep making mistakes.

The opposition changed things around a bit for this game. We never really got to grips with their new shape. And we made the kind of mistakes I just can't explain. We're going to have to look at what happened and make sure that, in future, we all understand what we're trying to do.
Are you frustrated not to have won this time round?
I'm sure you expected to follow up with another win against %1s. But today didn't go according to plan. How do you explain only getting a draw this time round?
The players looked tired to me.

The opposition played with more energy this time, for sure. I'm not looking for excuses but the lads have played a lot of football lately, and we looked second-best physically. The players need to rest and recover and cut out the mistakes we made today.
Football isn't always predictable.
Yes, we beat them last time but that doesn't always mean anything in the next game. I thought we played pretty well again. The boys put the effort in. perhaps today just wasn't meant to be our day.
We weren't good tactically.

They changed their team shape for the game today and we found ourselves getting outnumbered too often in dangerous areas of the pitch. Maybe we were low on energy. Or maybe we didn't deal with the tactical situation. Either way, we just weren't good enough, were we?
Have you got the edge on them now?
That's twice you've beaten %1s. Do you think you've proved you've got better players? Or is it just that you've worked out a way to play against them now?
You have to take pride in your work.

I have a lot of respect for %1s, of course. So we always think carefully about how to set up against them. But, once the game kicks off, it's all about the players. And we were stronger and quicker than them again today. All credit to the boys. They can be proud of their work.
It's all about players.

To be honest, we can prepare the team and give them a plan. But it's the boys themselves who have to go out and win the game. Every one of them gave everything today and they deserved the victory. Well done to them all!
Our attacking play is always a threat.

I think we look so dangerous going forward. This game was no different. The lads are in great form and I could tell straight away they were in the mood today. Our attacking play is always a threat. I was 100% confident we'd go on and win again.
Why do you struggle to break this team down?
Two draws against %1s. It seems you can't get the better of them. Do you think you're having problems up front at the moment?
It's a team game.

I wouldn't point to point the finger at any individual player. We've looked in decent form recently but %2s defended really well in both games and maybe we didn't do enough to support the man in possession and give him options. It's a team game, after all.
Well, something's not working.

Not scoring enough goals is an issue for us but the problem is something the whole team has to find a way to fix. Too many players are looking after themselves and not contributing to what we're trying to do as a team. We should be defending together and attacking together but that's not how it's working right now.
I know we can be better than that.

We've got plenty of talented players here at %1s, players you hope can win you games. And I know those can be more effective than they were today. We have to keep going and I'm sure winning performances will come soon enough.
Did your boys prove a point with the win today?

I think we took %1s by surprise.

Maybe %1s expected more of the same from us today. The lads worked really hard preparing for this game, though. They wanted to make sure we didn't let the fans down. We were more committed, more energetic. That's what I know this team's capable of.

I know people have wondered if we were good enough defensively after that draw last game. But I thought the lads responded really well today. They played as if they had a point to prove and we were dominant from start to finish.
